body:
Changelog:
- no more settings.txt
- new commands: config, cntcts, location, exit, notifications, beep, vibrate, community
- more options for the alias command
- new labels: storage, battery
- you can now see notifications directly in t-ui
- you can customize the format of available RAM, device name, time
- new tutorial: use the command to have a look
- bugfix

name: 5.3b
body:
- new settings (xml instead of txt)
- new commands: exit, config, beep, vibrate, tui, cntcts, location, notifications
- bugfix

- open url (search -u)
- CompareString won't be used when trying to launch an app 
- I suggest to use suggestions instead
- obviously, you can re-enable it in settings.txt
- bugfix/performance improvements
- fixed duplicated shell commands
- suggest most used apps
- bigger submit button
- fixed: keyboard covering output
- new icon

- donate command
- read contacts permission is now optional
- t-ui is able to detect physical keyboard enter key (settings.txt -> enableEnterInPhysicalKeyboard)
- bugfix
- multicolor suggestions
- touch a suggestion to execute a command
- more audio formats supported
